                      <div align="left">
                      <table border="0" width="696" height="136">
                        <tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-07-31 - Surefall Glade Festival on Morell-Thule</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> The Elves of Surefall, a guild on the Morell-Thule server, are hosting a festival in Surefall Glade this coming Sunday, August 6. The event will begin at 3:00 p.m. Eastern Standard Time and will run as long as there are people in attendance. Featured services will include a variety of tradespeople practicing fletching, blacksmithing, tailoring, and other skills as well as free starter weapons and provisions for newbies. Our casters will offer buffs to all, and there will even be music and fortune-telling. Some services may require a basic materials cost, but many will be free (donations will be cheerfully accepted in any case).

We are a roleplaying guild, and will be in character during the festival. Attendees are invited and strongly encouraged -- but not required -- to roleplay. We will provide safe escort from the Blackburrow entrance in Qeynos Hills and from the city gate in North Qeynos for those who require it. If you play (or are about to start playing) a new character, this event is an excellent place to get some help for little or no money. If you are not a newbie, there will still be much of interest, and we hope M-T players young and old will come and roleplay with us. 

Questions? E-mail Halwyn of Surefall at scholargipsy@hotmail.com or check out the Elves Website at www.geocities.com/loklorn to learn more about our guild. 

Thanks Halwyn!</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='55' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> Source: Halwyn -  </font> <a href=http://www.geocities.com/loklorn </a> www.geocities.com/loklorn </td></tr>    
